 ── Why Apache-2.0 for the SDK? ──
 The SDK is dual-licensed separately from the AGPL-3.0 core so that:
 - Tool vendors (Stream Deck, Razer, OBS plugin authors) can build engelOS
   integrations without AGPL compliance burden.
 - Companies whose policies forbid AGPL contributions (Google, Meta, Apple,
   many enterprises) can still build against the SDK and submit plugins.
 - Independent plugin authors can publish their plugins under any license
   they choose (MIT, BSD, proprietary, etc.).
 
 This follows the same pattern as Grafana (server AGPL, plugin SDK Apache)
 and Sentry (server BUSL, SDK MIT).

 See https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 for the actual license terms.
